			<h4><a rel="nofollow" id="comment_link_65472665" name="comment_link_65472665" href="//yro.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23726903&amp;cid=65472665" onclick="return D2.setFocusComment(65472665)" >Re:</a>


		 	<span id="comment_score_65472665" class="score"> (<a href="#" onclick="getModalPrefs('modcommentlog', 'Moderation Comment Log', 65472665); return false"><span class=opt>Score:</span>2</a>)</span></h4>
		</div>
		<div class="details">
			<span class="by"><span class="byby">by </span><a rel="nofollow" href="//slashdot.org/~DamnOregonian">DamnOregonian</a>  <span class="uid"><a rel="nofollow" href="//slashdot.org/~DamnOregonian">( 963763 )</a></span></a></span><span class="writes" style="display:none"> writes:</span> 
			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_65472665"></span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65472665"><p><div class="quote"><p>The illegality of downloading for personal use hinges on me making a copy on my personal device.</p></div><p>Not quite that simple. Fair use is a consideration for every copy made, period.<br>
<br>
Was your copy made to deprive the owner of money they would have otherwise made? Then no, it's not fair use, any any copy you make for that purpose is illegal.<br>
Was your copy made for a use that's protected under fair use? Then any copy you make for that purpose is legal.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_65472665">

